Magic Resistance and Psionic Resistance.

Magic and Psionic Resistance are very potent abilities
that allow a player or monster to become somewhat immune
to the effects of spells and/or certain types of attacks.
Because of this, much care must be used when adding an
object to the game that has these properties.  As a general
rule, any object that is not unique, should have at MOST
a 1% or 2% magic resistance(MR) OR Psionic resistance(PR), not
both.  Any object that gives both automatically becomes
a unique item.  Also, any object that gives more than a
one or two percent bonus qualifies as a unique item.
There should really be no objects in the game that give over
a 15% bonus total.  This means that if you have an object
that gives both a MR and PR bonus, when you total the bonus's
together, they should add up to at most 15%.  Also, and object
with a bonus higher than 10% should be carried by some sort of
legendary creature on the mud (like level 70 to 100 with special
abilities).  Objects that give bonuses in the 3% to 10% range
while unique and hopefully hard to obtain, should be within
the grasp of players other than the super high leveled ones.

From the perspective of the players, a player that has achieved
a MR or PR of 50% should be considered to have an awesome
defense.  Resistances higher than this should really be unattainable
by players.

The only real exception to the rule above, would be an object
that bestows a higher than normal MR or PR for a short duration.
These objects would still be considered unique as far as coding
rules go, but would allow for a higher than 15% bonus as long
as the duration was short-lived (few minutes or so) or there
was some other sort of high cost involved for the user to be able
to activate the resistance bonus (like a cost of 5 SP per second or
similar).  Either way, any object that gives over a 10% or 15% percent
bonus can only be temporary items with one or two uses maximum.

To use the the above commands, you would need to give the folloing
commands:

  this_player()->add_magic_resistance(1);
or
  this_player()->add_psi_resistance(1);

and to remove the bonus:

  this_player()->add_magic_resistance(-1);
or
  this_player()->add_psi_resistance(-1);



*************************IMPORTANT*********************************
IF YOU GIVE A BONUS TO A PLAYER FOR SAY "WEARING" AN ITEM, YOU MUST
ENSURE THAT WHEN THE ITEM IS REMOVED, THE BONUS IS ALSO REMOVED!!!!
*******************************************************************


